Mcaster1DSPEncoder — Authors and Attribution
==============================================

Maintainer
----------
Dave St. John <davestj@gmail.com>
  https://github.com/davestj
  Fork maintainer, VS2022 modernization, codec expansion, PortAudio
  integration, YAML configuration system, ICY 2.1 protocol work,
  ResizableLib UI modernization, Mcaster1 ecosystem integration.

Original Author — EdCast / Oddsock / AltaCast lineage
------------------------------------------------------
Ed Zaleski <ed@oddsock.org>
  https://www.oddsock.org/
  Author of the original Oddcast/EdCast DSP encoder suite on which this
  project is based. Architect of the core streaming engine, multi-encoder
  thread model, ICY/YP metadata handling, and the original Win32 MFC
  application framework.

  Ed Zaleski mentored Dave St. John in C/C++ and MFC Windows programming
  beginning in 2001, contributing directly to the early Castit broadcast
  infrastructure project at casterclub.com. His guidance and architectural
  input on backend streaming infrastructure were foundational to the
  Mcaster1 ecosystem.

AltaCast Fork
-------------
AltaCast was an intermediate fork of EdCast maintained by Ed Zaleski
and contributors at altacast.com. Mcaster1DSPEncoder inherits from the
AltaCast codebase.

Additional Credits
------------------
See CREDITS.md for full attribution history, dependency library credits,
and the story behind the fork.
